! scope="row" style="background:#ffdead;" | {{sortname|Friedrich|Olbricht}}?{{refn|[[Friedrich Olbricht]] was sentenced  to death by an impromptu [[court-martial]] in conjunction with the failed [[20 July plot]] of 1944 to kill [[Adolf Hitler]]. The execution was carried out immediately by [[firing squad]] at the [[Bendlerblock]] in Berlin. Olbricht was interred in full uniform with all orders and decorations. He was dishonorably discharged from the [[German Army (Wehrmacht)|Heer]] with the loss of all honors and military decorations on 4 August 1944. [[Heinrich Himmler]] ordered his earthly remains to be exhumed, burned and the ashes were dispersed.<ref>Scherzer 2007, p. 161.</ref>|group="Note"}}
